.TH LIVER 1 "2025" "liver" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
liver \- simple development web server with automatic live reload
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B liver
.RB \-d
.I directory
.RB [ \-p
.IR port ]
.RB [ \-w
.IR watch-dir ]
.RB [ \-n ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B liver
is a minimal HTTP server that automatically reloads browsers when files change.
It serves static files from a directory and watches for modifications, using
polling to notify connected clients.
.PP
When files in the watched directory are modified, the server updates an atomic
timestamp. Connected browsers poll /reload-time every 100ms and reload when the
timestamp changes.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-dir " " \fIpath\fR
Directory to serve (required).
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-port " " \fInumber\fR
Port to listen on. Default is 0 (automatic/ephemeral port).
.TP
.BR \-w ", " \-\-watch " " \fIpath\fR
Directory to watch for changes. Default is the same as
.BR \-\-dir .
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-no-browser
Don't automatically open browser. Default behavior is to open the browser
automatically.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
Serve current directory on random port:
.PP
.RS
.B liver \-d ./public
.RE
.PP
Serve on specific port, watch different directory:
.PP
.RS
.B liver \-d ./dist \-p 8080 \-w ./src
.RE
.PP
Serve without opening browser:
.PP
.RS
.B liver \-d ./public \-n
.RE
.SH IMPLEMENTATION
The server uses platform-specific file watching:
.IP \(bu 2
FSEvents on macOS
.IP \(bu 2
inotify on Linux
.IP \(bu 2
ReadDirectoryChangesW on Windows
.PP
The reload mechanism injects a small JavaScript snippet into HTML files that
polls the server for changes. No WebSocket connections are required.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /reload-time
Internal endpoint that returns the current reload timestamp. Polled by browsers
every 100ms.
.SH ATTRIBUTION
File watching implementations adapted from Zine by Loris Cro.
